  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Inclusive COVID-19 Healthcare and Social Protection for 
Older People in Pakistan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Launch a COVID-19 information campaign targeting at least 2,000 
older people.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provide financial support to 50 extremely poor 
COVID-19 positive older people</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Reduce ageist inequalities within the government COVID-19 social protection scheme
EHSAAS, increasing access to financial support for older people</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed project will be implemented locally in 
Pakistan&apos;s Nowshera District. Age International and 
international and national partners are well established in 
the area, where we have working together to champion
the health, wellbeing and inclusion of older people and 
reduce poverty and discrimination in older age for more 
than 15 years. This proposed project would be managed 
by Age International and implemented by Age Friendly 
Pakistan (FAID), one of our national partners and an 
expert in delivering programmes for older people since 
2005.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Train a COVID-19 healthcare surge team, enabling COVID-positive 
older people to access equipment, advice and support.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">directly protect and 
support at least 2,000 older people in Pakistan during coronavirus, and 
have the power to potentially reach up to 16,000 people.</narrative>
  </description>
